bfe4524f-c066-40b6-a312-8e84b6338272 Whisk the flour and cinnamon together in a separate bowl. Add the flour mixture to the bowl of an electric mixer. Place a large tea towel between the edge of the bowl and the electric mixer so that the flour won't escape. Mix on low speed for 30 seconds. Remove the tea towel and observe the dough mixing; when it starts to come together add the milk chocolate chips and mix until the dough clumps around the paddle attachment. Already mentioned, add flour if your dough is too sticky, and if it’s too dry, make sure you’ve mixed it as best as you can first, and if it’s still too dry, add a little water or milk until your dough comes together.

dfc32fd2-982c-4835-ba0f-acae75259cd8 Bake the cupcakes for 15-20 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick comes out clean. Remove the cupcakes from the oven and let them cool for at least 15 minutes before removing them from the tray.
dfc32fd2-982c-4835-ba0f-acae75259cd8 Allow cupcakes to cool completely and decorate!
bd1636e7-5258-4dbe-807f-0584cb8f5fbe In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment; mix butter and brown sugar on medium speed until fluffy. Scrape down the sides of the bowl and spatula as needed.
bd1636e7-5258-4dbe-807f-0584cb8f5fbe Mix in eggs, one at a time, and then molasses. Reduce speed to low. Scrape down bowl as needed.
bd1636e7-5258-4dbe-807f-0584cb8f5fbe Sift together flour, spices and salt and add to bowl; mix on low until just combined. Note that you would sift in the baking powder here as well, if you aren't concerned about the cookies spreading. Even environment and ingredients used affect baking, so if your dough is a bit sticky add flour until it's soft to the touch but doesn't stick to your fingers.
bd1636e7-5258-4dbe-807f-0584cb8f5fbe Roll dough out between parchment or the Dough E-Z mat, and let it rest by refrigerating until cold, about 1 hour.
bd1636e7-5258-4dbe-807f-0584cb8f5fbe Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Cut out cookie shapes and place on baking sheet lined with parchment paper, approximately 2 inches apart, and re-roll out dough and cut shapes as needed. Refrigerate until firm; at least 15 minutes to 1 hour.
bd1636e7-5258-4dbe-807f-0584cb8f5fbe Bake cookies until lightly golden; 10 to 14 minutes, depending on the size and thickness of the cookie. Let cool on sheets on wire racks and serve as is or decorate with royal icing.
34644d05-29e9-4601-9983-dbfc8d194de5 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Line your muffin tin with 24 regular sized baking cups.
34644d05-29e9-4601-9983-dbfc8d194de5 In a small bowl, mix the flour, cocoa and salt and set aside. In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, beat the butter and sugar on medium speed until mixed. Slowly add the eggs; beat 1 to 2 minutes or until light and fluffy. Add the red food color and vanilla and mix slowly until incorporated.
34644d05-29e9-4601-9983-dbfc8d194de5 Stir the vinegar into the buttermilk.
34644d05-29e9-4601-9983-dbfc8d194de5 On low speed, beat in 1/2 of the flour mixture just until mixed, then beat in 1/2 of the buttermilk mixture until mixed. Repeat beating in flour mixture alternately with the buttermilk just until mixed. Beat in the baking soda until mixed. Spoon about 1/4 cup of the batter into the cups.
34644d05-29e9-4601-9983-dbfc8d194de5 Bake about 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the cupcake comes out clean. Remove cupcakes from pan, cool completely and ice.
d9c25811-a622-440e-aede-598679a8b64e Cream the cream cheese, butter, and vanilla in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment.
d9c25811-a622-440e-aede-598679a8b64e Slowly add the icing sugar and beat until smooth.
d9c25811-a622-440e-aede-598679a8b64e Add 1 tsp white food gel coloring and mix until incorporated.
d9c25811-a622-440e-aede-598679a8b64e Once cupcakes have cooled, ice as desired.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Line your cupcake pan with cupcake liners.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Sift cocoa into a medium bowl. Slowly stir in the boiling water until smooth, then gradually whisk in milk. Set aside to cool.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Whisk together flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl. In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, or with an hand mixer on low speed, beat butter until fluffy; 3-5 minutes. Gradually beat in sugar, scraping down the sides of the bowl at least twice. Beat in the vanilla.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Add eggs in 3 batches, beating well after each addition. With the mixer on low speed, add flour mixture and reserved cocoa mixture a little at a time in alternate batches, starting and ending with the flour; beat until just combined.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Divide batter into the cupcake liners, 1/4 cup for each liner.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Bake for approximately 12-15 minutes or longer - until a toothpick or skewer comes out clean. Time will vary according to your oven.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 Take cupcake out and when cooled for about 5-10 minutes, remove from pans. Let cool completely and cut out a small hole in the top, center of each cupcake and fill with chilled dulce de leche. I only filled mine a little bit as I find it doesn't need a lot paired with the caramel icing.
f83e98ee-bdc9-497b-8057-139b2320d913 To finish, pipe caramel frosting onto cupcake with a large, round tip and place a gum paste leaf on top of the icing.
b826a749-9553-43f3-bf8e-19bab3b8a665 Place the cream cheese in a mixing bowl fitted with a paddle attachment, and mix on low speed until smooth and creamy.
b826a749-9553-43f3-bf8e-19bab3b8a665 Cream the butter and icing sugar in another mixing bowl until pale and fluffy.
b826a749-9553-43f3-bf8e-19bab3b8a665 Slowly add the cream cheese to the butter mixture and mix at medium-high speed until the frosting is combined.
b826a749-9553-43f3-bf8e-19bab3b8a665 Add the dulce de leche and mix until well incorporated and smooth.
b826a749-9553-43f3-bf8e-19bab3b8a665 Your frosting will be soft at this point. Chill in the refrigerator until set.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt into a bowl and set aside.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 In the bowl of a mixer fitted with a whisk attachment, or in a large bowl using an electric mixer on medium speed, beat the eggs and sugar until lightened to a cream color, about 2 minutes. During mixing, scrape down the sides of the bowl with a spatula as needed.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 On low speed, mix in the oil and vanilla until blended.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 Mix in the sour cream.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 Add in the flour mixture until it is incorporated and the batter is smooth.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 Stir in the cinnamon and mashed bananas.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 In a muffin tin lined with cupcake liners, fill each liner with 1/4 cup cup of the batter.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 Bake for approximately 25 minutes; until the top of the cupcake feels firm and an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
cbf0d5df-c2cc-4f65-9e1b-bcbee36376d3 Let the cupcakes cool completely and decorate.
bb2e4c3e-a2a0-4df6-8745-09e604976884 Cream the cream cheese, butter, and vanilla in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment.
bb2e4c3e-a2a0-4df6-8745-09e604976884 Slowly add the icing sugar and beat until smooth.
bb2e4c3e-a2a0-4df6-8745-09e604976884 Add 1 tsp white food gel coloring and mix until incorporated.
bb2e4c3e-a2a0-4df6-8745-09e604976884 Once cupcakes have cooled, ice as desired.
1d68f702-85aa-4244-a36a-db4da32c1386 In a food processor, pulse together raisins, currants, prunes, candied fruit and citrus peel until a smooth, thick paste forms. Transfer to a large bowl and stir in 2 cups (500 mL) of the rum. Cover tightly and keep in a cool, dark spot, stirring once a day, for at least 2 days, or for up to 2 months.
1d68f702-85aa-4244-a36a-db4da32c1386 In the bowl of an electric mixer, using the paddle attachment, beat butter and brown sugar until smooth. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Mix in coconut and almond extract.
1d68f702-85aa-4244-a36a-db4da32c1386 In a separate bowl, whisk together flour, almonds, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt; slowly stir into butter mixture until incorporated. Stir in raisin mixture and glacé cherries.
1d68f702-85aa-4244-a36a-db4da32c1386 Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).
1d68f702-85aa-4244-a36a-db4da32c1386 For cupcakes, line cupcake pans with liners, and using a ¼-cup (60-mL) measuring cup (or a #16 / 2 oz ice cream scoop), scoop the fruitcake batter into each liner. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
1d68f702-85aa-4244-a36a-db4da32c1386 For a Bundt cake, spray the Bundt cake pan with a nonstick cooking spray and pour the batter into the pan. Use a plastic spatula to evenly spread out the top of the batter. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
1d68f702-85aa-4244-a36a-db4da32c1386 Using a skewer, poke holes in the top of your cupcakes or cake and brush with rum. Let cool in the pan for 24 hours. Dust with icing sugar or top with luscious coconut cream cheese icing and sweetened coconut flakes.
fe779d56-1289-4a7f-995f-8ec8d65d8bea Cream the cream cheese, butter, and vanilla in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment.
fe779d56-1289-4a7f-995f-8ec8d65d8bea Slowly add the icing sugar and beat until smooth.
fe779d56-1289-4a7f-995f-8ec8d65d8bea Add 1 tsp white food gel coloring and mix until incorporated.
fe779d56-1289-4a7f-995f-8ec8d65d8bea Once cupcakes have cooled, ice as desired.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Preheat your oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Cream butter for about 3 minutes, scraping down sides of bowl occasionally.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Gradually add brown sugar, creaming after each addition. Set mixture aside.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Add to the creamed mixture in thirds, beating thoroughly after each addition.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Blend milk and maple syrup together.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Beating only until smooth after each addition, alternately add the dry ingredients and liquids to the creamed mixture.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Beat only until smooth and fill cupcake liners using an ice cream scoop.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Bake for approximately 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
e3054957-ecfb-4d29-b389-091260e30f68 Once cool, frost cupcakes.
fe184102-3aad-4cb8-8bae-2691618dfbef Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan, and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
fe184102-3aad-4cb8-8bae-2691618dfbef Increase heat and bring to a boil.
fe184102-3aad-4cb8-8bae-2691618dfbef Put candy thermometer in place and continue cooking without stirring. During cooking wash, sugar crystals from sides of pan with a pastry brush dipped in water. Cook until mixture reaches 238 degrees Fahrenheit.
fe184102-3aad-4cb8-8bae-2691618dfbef Remove pan to cooling rack and cool to lukewarm (about 110 degrees Fahrenheit), without stirring or moving the pan.
fe184102-3aad-4cb8-8bae-2691618dfbef Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon or electric mixer until mixture begins to lose its gloss and is of spreading consistency. Ice cupcakes. If frosting becomes too thick, beat in a few drops of cream or milk.
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit (180 degrees Celsius).
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a In a mixer bowl fitted with a paddle attachment, beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy (a few minutes).
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Beat in vanilla and then pumpkin spice.
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Stir dry mixture into wet (butter) mixture alternately with buttermilk, making 3 additions of dry ingredients and 3 of buttermilk.
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Using an ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup measurer, scoop batter into a muffin tin lined with cupcake liners.
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Bake for approximately 15-20 minutes, until cake tester (toothpicks or skewers work well too), inserted in centre comes out clean.
6ba81fd5-a120-4e7a-b524-85d336a8683a Let cool in muffin tins for about 5 minutes, then remove and let cool completely before adding icing.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit (180 degrees Celsius).
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 In a mixer bowl fitted with a paddle attachment, beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy (a few minutes).
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Beat in vanilla.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Stir dry mixture into wet (butter) mixture alternately with buttermilk, making 3 additions of dry ingredients and 3 of buttermilk.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Fold in 2 cups of blackberries.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Using an ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup measurer, scoop batter into a muffin tin lined with cupcake liners.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Bake for approximately 15-20 minutes, until cake tester (toothpicks or skewers work well too), inserted in centre comes out clean.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Let cool in muffin tins for about 5 minutes, then remove and let cool completely before adding icing.
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Icing recipe can also be found here .
aba94409-3d91-433c-9f39-85111b3c7ea2 Pipe a swirl of icing on top of cupcake, and roll the iced cupcakes in a bowl of sanding sugar. Top with a blackberry or decoration of choice and enjoy!
50e2b561-5b0f-4d94-84e4-048413f09f3e In the bowl of an electric mixer, using the paddle attachment, mix the Crisco All-vegetable shortening and clear vanilla extract on medium speed for about a minute. Scrape down the sides of the bowl.
50e2b561-5b0f-4d94-84e4-048413f09f3e Add the icing sugar and milk, cover the bowl with a large tea towel, and mix on low speed until the icing sugar is incorporated into the shortening. Take the tea towel away and mix until smooth.
50e2b561-5b0f-4d94-84e4-048413f09f3e Once your cupcakes are cool, ice them with a butter knife or large piping bag and tip of your choice. (I used Ateco #855, #856 and Wilton 1M).
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit or 180 degrees Celsius.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 In a bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, or in a large bowl, beat butter with sugar until fluffy.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Beat in lemon zest and lemon juice.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Whisk together the flour, baking powder and salt; stir into butter mixture alternately with milk, making 3 additions of dry ingredients and 2 of milk.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Fold raspberries into the batter.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Scoop into paper-lined or a greased muffin tin.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Bake in oven until a cake tester comes out clean, 20 - 25 minutes.
612fce54-0cf6-4f71-b624-e711ea4e8949 Transfer to rack an let cool before icing.
b9e72d33-8aa2-41eb-92a6-409ab91bd634 In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream butter until smooth and creamy, 2 to 3 minutes.
b9e72d33-8aa2-41eb-92a6-409ab91bd634 With the mixer on low speed, add 6 cups sugar, milk, and raspberry coulis; mix until light and fluffy. If necessary, gradually add remaining 2 cups sugar to reach desired consistency.
8183310e-263b-4c39-9812-03e1208c7d62 Preheat your oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit (180 degrees Celsius).
8183310e-263b-4c39-9812-03e1208c7d62 In a large bowl, beat butter with sugar until fluffy; beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
8183310e-263b-4c39-9812-03e1208c7d62 Beat in vanilla and chocolate sauce.
8183310e-263b-4c39-9812-03e1208c7d62 Whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into butter mixture alternately with sour cream, making 2 additions of dry ingredients and 2 additions of sour cream.
8183310e-263b-4c39-9812-03e1208c7d62 Using a piping bag or ziplock bag with the tip cut off, pipe the batter into the ice cream cones, filling to about 1cm from the top.
8183310e-263b-4c39-9812-03e1208c7d62 Bake in oven until cake tester comes out clean, about 20-25 minutes.
8183310e-263b-4c39-9812-03e1208c7d62 Transfer to rack to let cool.
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit (180 degrees Celsius).
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 In a mixer bowl fitted with a paddle attachment, beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy (a few minutes).
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Beat in vanilla.
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Stir dry mixture into wet (butter) mixture alternately with buttermilk, making 3 additions of dry ingredients and 3 of buttermilk.
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Using an ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup measurer, scoop batter into a muffin tin lined with cupcake liners.
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Bake for approximately 15-20 minutes, until cake tester (toothpicks or skewers work well too), inserted in centre comes out clean.
b979e070-e034-49d9-8cf5-e251f0fd9d36 Let cool in muffin tins for about 5 minutes, then remove and let cool completely before adding icing.
842b82af-3813-4256-bd74-c7b1a25049b6 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Place liners in cupcake pan.
842b82af-3813-4256-bd74-c7b1a25049b6 Cream the butter and 2 sugars on high speed until light and fluffy, approximately 5 minutes. (In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment is ideal, but a hand mixer can be used as well).
842b82af-3813-4256-bd74-c7b1a25049b6 Lower the speed to medium, add the eggs and the vanilla and mix well.
842b82af-3813-4256-bd74-c7b1a25049b6 In a separate bowl, whisk together the buttermilk and sour cream. In another bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt. On low speed, add the buttermilk mixture and the flour mixture alternately in thirds to the mixer bowl, beginning with the buttermilk mixture and ending with the flour mixture. Mix only until blended. Fold the batter with a rubber spatula to be sure it's completely blended.
842b82af-3813-4256-bd74-c7b1a25049b6 Divide the batter among the cupcake pans (about ¾ of the way for each cupcake). Bake in the middle of the oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes, remove from the pans, and allow to cool completely before frosting.
25cd5c79-ba8f-489b-b6a9-81544efcee7d Mix the confectioners' sugar, peanut butter, butter, vanilla, and salt together. (In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment is ideal, but a hand mixer can be used). Mix on medium-low speed until creamy.
25cd5c79-ba8f-489b-b6a9-81544efcee7d Add the cream and beat on high speed until the mixture is light and smooth.
25cd5c79-ba8f-489b-b6a9-81544efcee7d Garnish with mini Reese's cups or topper of your choice
af2d9d5b-7388-4d19-b2a3-6bb2ffbad952 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line muffin tin with paper liners.
af2d9d5b-7388-4d19-b2a3-6bb2ffbad952 Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger, into a medium bowl.
af2d9d5b-7388-4d19-b2a3-6bb2ffbad952 In a larger bowl, whisk together the eggs, pumpkin purée, granulated sugar, brown sugar, and vegetable oil. Add the flour mixture and stir until combined.
af2d9d5b-7388-4d19-b2a3-6bb2ffbad952 Divide the batter among the muffin tin and bake for about 20 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
af2d9d5b-7388-4d19-b2a3-6bb2ffbad952 Set pumpkin cupcakes aside to cool completely. These are delicious frosted with cream cheese icing or just as is!
c2b035d8-4811-4e58-af0e-83d8c7187af0 Cream the cream cheese, butter and maple syrup in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. Slowly add the icing sugar and beat until smooth.
c2b035d8-4811-4e58-af0e-83d8c7187af0 Once your cupcakes are cool, ice them with a butter knife or large piping bag and tip of your choice. (I used a large round tip – Ateco #809).
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Sift together the sugar, flour, freshly ground hazelnuts, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt; set aside.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 In a separate bowl, briefly whisk together the sour cream and vanilla extract; set aside.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 In the bowl of a mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, beat together the eggs, vegetable oil, and milk, until smooth.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Add the sour cream mixture and stir until well incorporated.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Add the flour mixture and stir on low speed until just incorporated. (The batter is fairly thin, don’t worry, you’ve done it correctly).
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Using an ice cream scoop, pour the batter into the cupcake liners (in muffin cupcake pan). Fill each liner no more than 2/3’s full.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Bake in preheated oven for about 20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. (Ovens vary). Cool in the pan for a few minutes, then remove from the pan, and allow to cool once again.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Optional – Nutella center: Fill a pastry bag fitted with a #10 circle piping tip, with Nutella. Insert the tip into the center of the cupcake, and squeeze for a few seconds.
73623561-ed9e-490d-a4f3-122357c8d916 Top cupcake with icing of your choice.
cf941f9c-6fb8-4f5b-a416-51c3145b6c23 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
cf941f9c-6fb8-4f5b-a416-51c3145b6c23 Beat the oil, sugar, and vanilla together in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment. Add the eggs, mixing briefly between each egg.
cf941f9c-6fb8-4f5b-a416-51c3145b6c23 In a different bowl, sift together the dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt cinnamon and nutmeg).
cf941f9c-6fb8-4f5b-a416-51c3145b6c23 With the mixer on low speed, add 1/2 of the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients. Add the grated carrots and raisins to the remaining flour, mix well, and add to the batter. Mix until just combined.
cf941f9c-6fb8-4f5b-a416-51c3145b6c23 Using an ice cream scoop, spoon the batter into cupcake liners (in your muffin pan), until each is 3/4 full.
cf941f9c-6fb8-4f5b-a416-51c3145b6c23 Bake at 350 degrees Fahrenheit for 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool.
93075e55-57d4-474d-9d27-e9f841e6a603 Cream the cream cheese, butter, and vanilla in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment.
93075e55-57d4-474d-9d27-e9f841e6a603 Slowly add the icing sugar and beat until smooth.
93075e55-57d4-474d-9d27-e9f841e6a603 Add 1 tsp white food gel coloring and mix until incorporated.

aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line your muffin tin with liners.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca In a large bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca In a separate bowl, combine the sour cream and vanilla extract. Set aside.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment, combine the butter and sugar and beat on medium speed until smooth.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Set the mixer to low speed and add the eggs, one at a time, scraping thoroughly between each addition.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Alternately add the flour and sour cream mixtures to the butter mixture in two batches, starting and ending with the flour mixture. Scrape down the bowl after each addition.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Gradually pour in the coffee. Scrape down the bowl and beat until thoroughly combined.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Scoop the batter into your cupcake liners with a spoon or ice cream scoop.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Bake for 26 minutes or until the center of the cupcake has just set. (I insert a barbeque skewer to check).
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Take out the cupcakes, make a little hole in the center with a knife and insert a Turtle chocolate as far as the cupcake allows.
aa388994-cc1b-468b-a4db-7c375e39b9ca Bake for another 4 minutes. Once cupcakes have cooled and you’ve removed them from the muffin tin, top with chocolate icing and *optional toppings.
509d9dfc-1a2a-4a9b-9a2c-5165ce61a7b7 Use a double boiler to melt the chocolate and cream together. (Make your own version by placing a glass or stainless steel bowl on top of a pot with simmering water). Stir occasionally until the chips are melted.
509d9dfc-1a2a-4a9b-9a2c-5165ce61a7b7 Off the heat, stir in the corn syrup and vanilla and allow the mixture to cool to room temperature.
509d9dfc-1a2a-4a9b-9a2c-5165ce61a7b7 In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, whisk the chocolate mixture, softened butter and icing sugar on medium speed for a few minutes, until it has thickened.
bb30be2f-8189-4640-bb77-a4d353533941 In mixer bowl, pour in the warm water and the meringue powder. Mix it with a whisk by hand until it is frothy and thickened…about 30 seconds.
bb30be2f-8189-4640-bb77-a4d353533941 Add in caramel flavoring and whisk for a few seconds.
bb30be2f-8189-4640-bb77-a4d353533941 Sift the icing sugar. Pour all the icing sugar into the mixer bowl.
bb30be2f-8189-4640-bb77-a4d353533941 Using the paddle attachment on the LOWEST speed, mix slowly for a full 10 minutes. Icing will get thick and creamy.
bb30be2f-8189-4640-bb77-a4d353533941 Cover the bowl with a dampened tea-towel to prevent crusting and drying.
bb30be2f-8189-4640-bb77-a4d353533941 Cover the bowl with a dampened tea-towel to prevent crusting and drying.Tint with food colorings or thin the icing with small amounts of warm water to reach the desired consistency.
b0f98b44-692d-4453-b57c-c35cc995f41d In mixer bowl, pour in the warm water and the meringue powder. Mix it with a whisk by hand until it is frothy and thickened…about 30 seconds.
b0f98b44-692d-4453-b57c-c35cc995f41d Sift the icing sugar and cocoa powder together. Give it a whisk to make sure the cocoa powder is incorporated fairly evenly.
b0f98b44-692d-4453-b57c-c35cc995f41d Pour in all the icing sugar and cocoa powder at once and place the bowl on the mixer.
b0f98b44-692d-4453-b57c-c35cc995f41d Using the paddle attachment on the LOWEST speed, mix slowly for a full 10 minutes. Icing will get thick and creamy.
b0f98b44-692d-4453-b57c-c35cc995f41d Cover the bowl with a dampened tea-towel to prevent crusting and drying.
b0f98b44-692d-4453-b57c-c35cc995f41d Tint with food colorings and/or thin the icing with small amounts of warm water to reach the desired consistency.
8db50b6d-8c87-4acf-8f37-75047040d360 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
8db50b6d-8c87-4acf-8f37-75047040d360 Cream the coconut oil and coconut sugar in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, on high speed, for approximately 3 minutes. You may need to occasionally scrape down the sides of the bowl and the attachment.
8db50b6d-8c87-4acf-8f37-75047040d360 With the mixer on low speed, add the eggs, one at a time, letting each egg be mixed in before you add the next, and scraping down the bowl after each addition. Add the vanilla extract and mix.
8db50b6d-8c87-4acf-8f37-75047040d360 In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. In two parts, alternately add the dry ingredients and the buttermilk to the batter, beginning and ending with the dry. Mix until just barely combined. Fold in the finely crushed coconut chips.
8db50b6d-8c87-4acf-8f37-75047040d360 Line a muffin tin with paper liners. Fill each liner with batter, until about ¾ full. Bake for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Allow cupcakes to cool for about 15 minutes and then remove to a baking rack to completely cool.
8db50b6d-8c87-4acf-8f37-75047040d360 Garnish with icing or serve as is!
4a0729cc-57a1-4bab-9a55-c8a4466e78c4 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line muffin tin with paper liners.
4a0729cc-57a1-4bab-9a55-c8a4466e78c4 Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger, into a medium bowl.
4a0729cc-57a1-4bab-9a55-c8a4466e78c4 In a larger bowl, whisk together the eggs, pumpkin purée, granulated sugar, brown sugar, and Crisco pure vegetable oil. Add the flour mixture and stir until combined.
4a0729cc-57a1-4bab-9a55-c8a4466e78c4 Divide the batter among the muffin tin and bake for about 20 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
4a0729cc-57a1-4bab-9a55-c8a4466e78c4 Set pumpkin cupcakes aside to cool completely. Frost with icing.
c7918e7a-397a-4999-a6d9-84e8496896bf In the bowl of an electric mixer, using the paddle attachment, mix the Crisco All-vegetable shortening and clear vanilla extract on medium speed for about a minute. Scrape down the sides of the bowl.
c7918e7a-397a-4999-a6d9-84e8496896bf Add the icing sugar and milk, cover the bowl with a large tea towel, and mix on low speed until the icing sugar is incorporated into the shortening. Take the tea towel away and mix until smooth.
c7918e7a-397a-4999-a6d9-84e8496896bf Once your cupcakes are cool, ice them with a butter knife or large piping bag and tip of your choice. (I used Ateco #855, #856 and Wilton 1M).
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Preheat your oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Cream butter for about 3 minutes, scraping down sides of bowl occasionally.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Gradually add brown sugar, creaming after each addition. Set mixture aside.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Add to the creamed mixture in thirds, beating thoroughly after each addition.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Blend milk and maple syrup together.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Beating only until smooth after each addition, alternately add the dry ingredients and liquids to the creamed mixture.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Beat only until smooth and fill cupcake liners using an ice cream scoop.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Bake for approximately 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
9174f735-6db7-43aa-86c1-bd0cc5178587 Once cool, frost cupcakes.
98d93721-477a-4d45-b1d1-e856e84b0795 Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan, and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
98d93721-477a-4d45-b1d1-e856e84b0795 Increase heat and bring to a boil.
98d93721-477a-4d45-b1d1-e856e84b0795 Put candy thermometer in place and continue cooking without stirring. During cooking wash, sugar crystals from sides of pan with a pastry brush dipped in water. Cook until mixture reaches 238 degrees Fahrenheit.
98d93721-477a-4d45-b1d1-e856e84b0795 Remove pan to cooling rack and cool to lukewarm (about 110 degrees Fahrenheit), without stirring or moving the pan.
98d93721-477a-4d45-b1d1-e856e84b0795 Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon or electric mixer until mixture begins to lose its gloss and is of spreading consistency. Ice cupcakes. If frosting becomes too thick, beat in a few drops of cream or milk.
cd10b046-ad88-4d26-ace9-19973782d5cd In the bowl of stand mixer, using a paddle attachment, whip butter and cocoa powder together until well incorporated.
cd10b046-ad88-4d26-ace9-19973782d5cd Add icing sugar, stir, and slowly pour in milk until mixed. Add in vanilla extract and mix.
cd10b046-ad88-4d26-ace9-19973782d5cd Using a rubber spatula, scrape down the sides of the bowl and whip on medium speed until light and fluffy (approximately 1 minute).
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit or 180 degrees Celsius.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d In a bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, or in a large bowl, beat butter with sugar until fluffy.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Beat in lemon zest and lemon juice.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Whisk together the flour, baking powder and salt; stir into butter mixture alternately with milk, making 3 additions of dry ingredients and 2 of milk.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Fold raspberries into the batter.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Scoop into paper-lined or a greased muffin tin.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Bake in oven until a cake tester comes out clean, 20 - 25 minutes.
189bbfb2-9e8f-49da-8d6a-e7fe118db48d Transfer to rack an let cool before icing.
1df4f9af-0b12-436b-80e2-2ce2d18eeb12 In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, cream butter until smooth and creamy, 2 to 3 minutes.
1df4f9af-0b12-436b-80e2-2ce2d18eeb12 With the mixer on low speed, add 6 cups sugar, milk, and raspberry coulis; mix until light and fluffy. If necessary, gradually add remaining 2 cups sugar to reach desired consistency.
18e07aed-0cc0-4ec6-98e0-9be74c8309d3 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F. Place liners in cupcake pan.
18e07aed-0cc0-4ec6-98e0-9be74c8309d3 Cream the butter and 2 sugars on high speed until light and fluffy, approximately 5 minutes. (In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment is ideal, but a hand mixer can be used as well).
18e07aed-0cc0-4ec6-98e0-9be74c8309d3 Lower the speed to medium, add the eggs and the vanilla and mix well.
18e07aed-0cc0-4ec6-98e0-9be74c8309d3 In a separate bowl, whisk together the buttermilk and sour cream. In another bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt. On low speed, add the buttermilk mixture and the flour mixture alternately in thirds to the mixer bowl, beginning with the buttermilk mixture and ending with the flour mixture. Mix only until blended. Fold the batter with a rubber spatula to be sure it's completely blended.
18e07aed-0cc0-4ec6-98e0-9be74c8309d3 Divide the batter among the cupcake pans (about ¾ of the way for each cupcake). Bake in the middle of the oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes, remove from the pans, and allow to cool completely before frosting.
31938a3f-aaa3-44d5-84b0-3f417405d38c Mix the confectioners' sugar, peanut butter, butter, vanilla, and salt together. (In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment is ideal, but a hand mixer can be used). Mix on medium-low speed until creamy.
31938a3f-aaa3-44d5-84b0-3f417405d38c Add the cream and beat on high speed until the mixture is light and smooth.
31938a3f-aaa3-44d5-84b0-3f417405d38c Garnish with mini Reese's cups or topper of your choice
a642e92b-66c1-4243-8478-f5b5c167e4c8 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Line muffin tin with paper liners.
a642e92b-66c1-4243-8478-f5b5c167e4c8 Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger, into a medium bowl.
a642e92b-66c1-4243-8478-f5b5c167e4c8 In a larger bowl, whisk together the eggs, pumpkin purée, granulated sugar, brown sugar, and vegetable oil. Add the flour mixture and stir until combined.
a642e92b-66c1-4243-8478-f5b5c167e4c8 Divide the batter among the muffin tin and bake for about 20 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
a642e92b-66c1-4243-8478-f5b5c167e4c8 Set pumpkin cupcakes aside to cool completely. These are delicious frosted with cream cheese icing or just as is!
251e50fc-c618-45e7-b2aa-a275e1ab2d0f Cream the cream cheese, butter and maple syrup in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. Slowly add the icing sugar and beat until smooth.
251e50fc-c618-45e7-b2aa-a275e1ab2d0f Once your cupcakes are cool, ice them with a butter knife or large piping bag and tip of your choice. (I used a large round tip – Ateco #809).
4fc84d66-24b1-449f-84b5-61c41247a161 Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.
4fc84d66-24b1-449f-84b5-61c41247a161 Beat the oil, sugar, and vanilla together in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment. Add the eggs, mixing briefly between each egg.
4fc84d66-24b1-449f-84b5-61c41247a161 In a different bowl, sift together the dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt cinnamon and nutmeg).
4fc84d66-24b1-449f-84b5-61c41247a161 With the mixer on low speed, add 1/2 of the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients. Add the grated carrots and raisins to the remaining flour, mix well, and add to the batter. Mix until just combined.
4fc84d66-24b1-449f-84b5-61c41247a161 Using an ice cream scoop, spoon the batter into cupcake liners (in your muffin pan), until each is 3/4 full.
4fc84d66-24b1-449f-84b5-61c41247a161 Bake at 350 degrees Fahrenheit for 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Let cool.
a45d11bc-5ac0-4aae-8651-c7dc90757e5a Cream the cream cheese, butter, and vanilla in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with a paddle attachment.
a45d11bc-5ac0-4aae-8651-c7dc90757e5a Slowly add the icing sugar and beat until smooth.
a45d11bc-5ac0-4aae-8651-c7dc90757e5a Add 1 tsp white food gel coloring and mix until incorporated.
a45d11bc-5ac0-4aae-8651-c7dc90757e5a Once cupcakes have cooled, ice as desired.
